  "instructions": [
    "Combine Japanese onion and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, or until the onion is tender and the liquid has evaporated.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together rice vinegar, sugar, and sesame oil to make the dressing.",
    "To assemble the donburi, place the ti-leaf wrap on a flat surface and spread the chopped Japanese onion on one half of the wrap.",
    "Drizzle the dressing over the onion and sprinkle with sesame seeds and green onions.",
    "Fold the other half of the ti-leaf wrap over the filling to enclose the donburi.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
